<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2610</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bluefields</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sanders</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bluefields</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-15"><hi rend="italic">July 15,
                                    1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July
                                25.</hi>]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 291</seg></opener>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>As for the expulsion decree incident, however, I am glad to report that I
                            consider the matter closed; …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>… the decree was shortly ordered suspended. According to my private
                            information, it was so ordered on June the 25th. The Governor of
                            Bluefields got the news officially on the 28th. …</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John O. Sanders</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>